ll MF. Current practical applications of diagnostic immunohistochemistry in breast pathology. <em>Am J Surg Pathol</em> 2004;28(8):1076–1091.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1097/01.pas.0000126780.10029.f0">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15252316/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Current+practical+applications+of+diagnostic+immunohistochemistry+in+breast+pathology&amp;author=MF+Lerwill&amp;publication_year=2004&amp;journal=Am+J+Surg+Pathol&amp;pages=1076-1091&amp;doi=10.1097%2F01.pas.0000126780.10029.f0&amp;pmid=15252316">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Bonacho T, Rodrigues F, Liberal J. Immunohistochemistry for diagnosis and prognosis of breast cancer: a review. <em>Biotech Histochem</em> 2020;95(2):71–91.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1080/10520295.2019.1651901">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31502889/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Immunohistochemistry+for+diagnosis+and+prognosis+of+breast+cancer%3A+a+review&amp;author=T+Bonacho&amp;author=F+Rodrigues&amp;author=J+Liberal&amp;publication_year=2020&amp;journal=Biotech+Histochem&amp;pages=71-91&amp;doi=10.1080%2F10520295.2019.1651901&amp;pmid=31502889">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">10.</div><div id="r10" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Brogi E, Krystel-Whittemore M. Papillary neoplasms of the breast including upgrade rates and management of intraductal papilloma without atypia diagnosed at core needle biopsy. <em>Mod Pathol</em> 2021;34(Suppl 1):78–93.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41379-020-00706-5">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33106592/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Papillary+neoplasms+of+the+breast+including+upgrade+rates+and+management+of+intraductal+papilloma+without+atypia+diagnosed+at+core+needle+biopsy&amp;author=E+Brogi&amp;author=M+Krystel-Whittemore&amp;publication_year=2021&amp;journal=Mod+Pathol&amp;pages=78-93&amp;doi=10.1038%2Fs41379-020-00706-5&amp;pmid=33106592">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">11.</div><div id="r11" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Patel BK, Falcon S, Drukteinis J. Management of nipple discharge and the associated imaging findings. <em>Am J Med</em> 2015;128(4):353–360.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.amjmed.2014.09.031">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25447625/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Management+of+nipple+discharge+and+the+associated+imaging+findings&amp;author=BK+Patel&amp;author=S+Falcon&amp;author=J+Drukteinis&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Am+J+Med&amp;pages=353-360&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.amjmed.2014.09.031&amp;pmid=25447625">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="r12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Tabár L, Dean PB, Péntek Z. Galactography: the diagnostic procedure of choice for nipple discharge. <em>Radiology</e